1
00:00:11,940 --> 00:00:14,580
Sorry I'm late today.

2
00:00:16,580 --> 00:00:18,840
You're still homeless, huh?

3
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:32,450
This nation really will fall
due to incompetent politicians.

4
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:35,630
Those damn nepo-baby Diet members—

5
00:00:37,670 --> 00:00:42,200
Mom, I've been wondering.
Why do you turn off the TV?

6
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:48,330
Because we're gonna eat.
Come on, sit up straight.

7
00:00:50,290 --> 00:00:54,360
You always turn off the TV
when Donraku comes on.

8
00:00:56,670 --> 00:00:59,760
We promised not to talk about that anymore.

9
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:02,780
We used to have tons of pictures of him up.

10
00:01:02,780 --> 00:01:04,290
How long are you gonna hide it?

11
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:06,600
I might see him in Tokyo.

12
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:08,690
I'm saying this for your sake.

13
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:13,560
Once you grow up, someday you'll
understand, whether you like it or not.

14
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:21,350
Um, excuse me. Is the
audition in this building?

15
00:01:21,350 --> 00:01:24,100
I dunno. Look it up yourself, why don't you?

16
00:01:26,490 --> 00:01:27,660
Are you auditioning today?

17
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:30,090
Huh? Uh, yes.

18
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:31,490
Then let's go together.

19
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:41,500
Thank you for earlier.

20
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:45,660
It's totally fine. That map
was impossible to understand.

21
00:01:45,660 --> 00:01:49,280
Yeah. I just came to Tokyo yesterday.

22
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,100
What? Wow.

23
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,600
That must've made it
even harder to understand.

24
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:54,860
Where are you from?

25
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:56,100
Oita.

26
00:01:56,510 --> 00:01:58,760
Is that why your backpack's so big?

27
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:01,520
I even packed everything I need.

28
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:03,020
What? Really?

29
00:02:03,020 --> 00:02:04,650
You didn't bring anything?

30
00:02:05,740 --> 00:02:11,250
Oh, right. I didn't notice.

31
00:02:11,990 --> 00:02:17,030
You seem so calm. You're not nervous at all.

32
00:02:18,380 --> 00:02:20,380
I actually just noticed
since you mentioned it,

33
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:26,250
but I seem to have forgotten my bag
 at home because I was so nervous.

34
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:31,970
What? Seriously?

35
00:02:33,230 --> 00:02:36,050
I'm Mitsuya Yuki. Nice to meet you.

36
00:02:36,050 --> 00:02:39,870
I thought if I became an idol
I'd be able to meet my dad.

37
00:02:39,870 --> 00:02:43,700
That's a nice dream.
I'm sure it'll come true.

38
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:47,300
Why did you audition, Mitsuya-san?

39
00:02:48,810 --> 00:02:51,480
I think my reason's a bit like yours.

40
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:56,670
Like my father, I wanted to
make people laugh and cry.

41
00:02:56,990 --> 00:03:00,400
I wanted to get a job in entertainment
that would let me move people's hearts.

42
00:03:01,580 --> 00:03:04,210
That's amazing! Your dad's an entertainer?

43
00:03:04,210 --> 00:03:07,270
Oh, but I didn't tell him I'm auditioning.

44
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:11,760
My father said he'd introduce me
to some people in the business he knows,

45
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,630
but then I wouldn't be
doing it myself, you know?

46
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,880
That sounds like a wasted opportunity.

47
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,220
Not at all.

48
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:20,990
I don't want people to say I only
got the job because of my father.

49
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:26,030
He honed his art all on his own.

50
00:03:26,730 --> 00:03:27,980
Huh.

51
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:29,720
I'm kind of jealous.

52
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:32,890
Oh, sorry. I shouldn't have said all that.

53
00:03:32,890 --> 00:03:34,630
Sorry. Forget what I said.

54
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:38,090
It's totally fine. I'm used to it.

55
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:45,640
It'd be great if we both passed the audition.

56
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:48,000
I had the same thought!

57
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,970
Really?

58
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:21,310
Sorry, I know this was sudden!

59
00:04:21,310 --> 00:04:22,410
It's fine.

60
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:26,460
I was glad to hear from you, Mitsuya-san.

61
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:28,890
So, listen...

62
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,730
Yeah?

63
00:04:30,730 --> 00:04:32,540
I got a call after that.

64
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:33,080
Yeah.

65
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:36,110
They called me in for a final screening.

66
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:38,420
Really? That's great!

67
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:40,740
I wanted to tell you in person.

68
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:45,340
What about you, Sakura-chan?
Did you get your results yet?

69
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:48,100
No, nothing.

70
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,830
Then you still have a chance.

71
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:50,640
Really?

72
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:54,860
They're still deciding.
They didn't tell me anything else.

73
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:59,070
But I'm sure you'd pass another audition.

74
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:05,200
Yeah. I'm broke, so I can't
even go back home now.

75
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:09,390
If it comes to it, I'll ask
my father if he has any ideas.

76
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:12,050
What does your dad do?

77
00:05:12,610 --> 00:05:15,230
Oh, right. Sorry.

78
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,210
You don't have to hide it.

79
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:20,170
It's embarrassing.

80
00:05:20,170 --> 00:05:23,280
What? Why? You should hold your head high.

81
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:26,810
You passed the audition on your own merits.

82
00:05:27,490 --> 00:05:31,230
My dad is a storyteller.
Do you know about rakugo?

83
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:32,390
Yeah.

84
00:05:32,780 --> 00:05:35,330
He's on TV a lot.

85
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:38,520
He had a reputation for casually
saying things that upset people,

86
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,400
so I was a little embarrassed about it.

87
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:44,820
Maybe you know him. His name is Donraku.

88
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,370
Huh...

89
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:52,450
Mitsuya Yuki

90
